      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 106: This block introduces a malformed make fragment: `VPX_CONF +\u003d \\` is followed by `LOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d...`, then `LOCAL_HOSTVARS` is reassigned again, and there is an unmatched `endif`. This will either make `make` fail with a conditional syntax error or append `LOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d...` to `VPX_CONF` instead of setting the environment. Keep the macOS-specific deployment target and C++ flags inside the `ifdef HAVE_MACOSX` block only. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nifdef HAVE_MACOSX\nVPX_CONF +\u003d --extra-cxxflags\u003d\"$(EXTRA_COMMON) $(EXTRA_CXXFLAGS)\"\nLOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d$(HOSTVARS) MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET\u003d$(MIN_OSX_VERSION)\nendif\n```",
